rComments: She is nice enough, but her feedback on projects can be condescending. She is a fair marker but the amount of work to be done for participation marks was insane and WAY too much. This will make me never take a class with her again. She knows tech well but she seems to think that bc it was an online class she can assign an infinite amount of work.

Extremely competent is probably the best way to describe her. Very tech-savvy as well, which was refreshing and made for an interactive and engaging class. As long as u show up and do the work, which isn't heavy, you will do well. Would definitely recommend
This professor was just okay nothing special. Have definitely had better FLS professors. Wouldn't be my first choice, but wouldn't be mad to take another class with her.

The content of the course was very random and sometimes hard to work with. Her projects were fair as far as difficulty and were graded very fairly but they were annoying to do. The feedback given on the assignments sometimes made no sense but she is easy to reach via email and answers questions efficiently. She will give extensions is needed

Very nice professor! She is super friendly and she structured her online classes well! Took the course out of curiosity and ended up enjoying it. The workload is a bit more than your average course but it isn't too difficult.

She is a really great professor, I always enjoyed going to her class. Clear expectations, great feedback and very relevant assignments which were usually pretty enjoyable to complete. Especially curing COVID her clear class structure and kindness were appreciated.

I really enjoyed her class, material and discussions were engaging. She assigns multiple small assignments throughout the semester and the final is based on the assignments done already on a smaller scale i.e short podcast. I always looked forward to going to her class. Her online classes are structured really well, great during a pandemic.
She's nice enough, but can be a little patronizing in addressing her students and giving lectures. Heavy workload.

She is a really nice lady, willing to help her students outside of class. She answers emails relatively quickly. It was her first time teaching an online class and would say she did a good job. A lot of assignments that she assigns that are sometimes difficult/hard to complete. grading  little assignments + participation + big assignments + final

Extremely nice. If you don't do the homework, it's not a big deal. Always willing to go above and beyond to help you and make sure you understand. Never makes you feel stupid if you get the wrong answer. Very positive teacher.

She's an amazing professor! She gives her students a lot of online resources in order to improve their French speaking, and has us take part in interactive activities where we are all able to practice our French in a friendly environment. :)

She is so friendly and is always available if you have questions. She lets you use online translators during all of the evaluations and exams and most of them are take-home. I cannot emphasize enough how supportive she is! I decided to minor in French because of her. 10/10 would recommend! I take all of my FLS courses with her.

Super fun and interactive activities of the day. literally all you have to do is go to class. if you don't you literally not pass. She speaks clearly and slowly so it's easy to understand her. Pretty chill. assignments are easy and we're allowed to use resources. exam is soft, i got a 96 on the written part. also this was a hybrid course - cool!

Very approachable, always willing to help, and provides very good feedback on all assignments. She provides students with all of the tools needed to succeeded and the assignments always interesting. The hybrid option made the course even better, since students could use a variety applications to improve their French remotely.
Almost everything is done in class. If you don't show up, you will literally fail. If you do, you should have no problem scoring an A.

This prof is amazing! She really cares for her students and wants them to do well. She also speaks French nice and slow so it' easy to understand. We had written assignments every week. There were basically two types of assignments, individual and partner (not as bad as group work :P). As long as you follow her criteria, you'll do really well.

This is the first hybrid course I've taken, and I love it! Prof. Rheaume is also the best French teacher I have ever had! She makes the class interesting, and the interactive material she chooses makes you want to keep learning. She also gives great feedback and helps with everything. If all my French teachers had been this great, I'd be fluent!

For my first hybrid class at uOttawa, this was pretty ok! It was kind of annoying, relearning the passe compose or subjonctif for the fourth time, but the class was all in all not that hard. The grading scheme is a bit confusing, especially with all the assignments you do. Would take a class with her again! She's so nice!

Never clear on assignments & inconsistent grading Multiple assignments due every week Accused me of plagiarism, refused to believe I didn't because according to her it was "way above" my skill level. One email, "My joy and comfort is to know that I have the chance to have students like you"  Next email she called me a bad student (I get mainly Bs)

Very easy grader, just show that you put an effort into the assignments and you'll do well. She used to be a high school teacher so the assignments are very childish and irrelevant. Some assignments had to be finished by the end of the class and never gave us enough time to finish them. Very chill prof overall though.
Pretty easy. Class participation is required and you're set for the exam. She did used to be a high school teacher so most of the things did seem childish, but she was a pretty caring woman overall.

I took a hybrid online/in-class course and was pleasantly surprised with how helpful the prof was. She explained concepts well and gave lots of small assignments to take the pressure off. Some of the content we covered seemed pointless but did make it less bland than it could've been. Definitely noticed major improvement  French after her class.

Took her class this past winter. Awesome professor. Very little reading, exam was engaging, and she is very pro-Antidote even for the final exam (BYOD). She was kind and approachable, and she never singled anyone out. I found her marking criteria to be rather lax. Two major projects and a final exam based on a theatre piece and a Quebec movie.
Not helpful nor encouraging. Doesn't put much effort into the class either and the assignments seem childish.
